FBIS4-65898 "drweu101_q_94001" FBIS-WEU-94-101 Daily Report 24 May 1994 TURKEY President Demirel Congratulates Herzog on Election President Demirel Congratulates Herzog on Election TA2405180794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1500 GMT 24 May 94 TA2405180794 Ankara TRT Television Network Turkish BFN [Announcer-read report] [Text] President Suleyman Demirel has stated that the Turkish people give special importance to furthering Turkish-German relations. Demirel sent a congratulatory message to Roman Herzog on his election as Germany's president. According to a statement issued by the Press Center of the President's Office, Demirel wished Herzog success in his new appointment. The statement further notes: The Turkish nation attaches special importance to furthering relations with Germany because of the deep-rooted historical ties between the two countries and the 2 million Turkish citizens living in Germany. Expressing his belief that the traditional Turkish-German cooperation and friendliness will be furthered during Herzog's term, Demirel added that he is always ready and willing to cooperate on this issue.
